Author: sreyalsedahs
Text: Same here. My dentist just gave me a mouthguard to wear at night so I don't grind my teeth into oblivion, but my jaw still pops. Got told surgery could go very badly so I guess I'm just waiting for the arthritis to kick in :/

Author: fishonthesun
Text: Had TMJ a while ago, it's gotten bad again from restricting I think. But the most my dentist did was give me a mouthguard to wear at night and tell me no more ice chewing or gum chewing. And he wanted me to use my fist to stop yawns from going past a certain point
